article.description: — Dwayne Cohill had 26 points in Youngstown State's 76-65 victory against Central Michigan on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Youngstown State defeats Central Michigan 76-65
article.story:
MOUNT PLEASANT, Mich. -- — Dwayne Cohill had 26 points in Youngstown State's 76-65 victory against Central Michigan on Wednesday night.

Cohill had three steals for the Penguins (9-4). Malek Green added 16 points and Brandon Rush scored 15.

Brian Taylor finished with 15 points for the Chippewas (4-8). Markus Harding added 14 points and Jesse Zarzuela had 11 points and seven assists.

------
